Why are there varieties of organisms? How do they co-exist in such a diverse world? How such biodiversity has evolved? Why and how are they locally or globally in danger of decline or extinct? In this class, you will learn about the meaning, mechanisms, evolution, and conservation of biodiversity. First, you will learn the state of biodivresity on earth and the evolutionary process of biodiversity. Second, you will learn the distribution, abundance and interrelationships of animals and plants, and understand the structure and function of ecosystems. It is shown here that remote ecosystems are linked by air, water, and migratory animals. Finally, you will learn ways of the conservation of endangered species and ecosystems, and discuss how we can have good relationships with nature and wildlife.

